    "description": "Per the regulatory submission plan and ASME V&V 40 Section 6 guidance, verification of the FEA model's predictive accuracy for construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement SHALL be performed via a controlled experiment in which all boundary conditions, loading rates, and specimen preparation steps are prospectively specified and independently replicated. This requirement ensures that systematic sources of variability are isolated and that the comparison between model output and physical measurement is inferentially valid.",
