      "name": "F1717 compression-bending validation result — non-cannulated 7.5 mm construct",
      "description": "The FEA ensemble predictions for construct stiffness (mean 187 N/mm), yield force (mean 412 N), and force at 40 mm displacement (mean 638 N) were compared against N=11 physical specimens tested across two independent laboratories following ASTM F1717. All QoI differences fell within the pre-specified 10% acceptance bound, and all E/uval ratios remained below 1.96, confirming adequate predictive accuracy. The activity drew on retrospectively collated test records from both laboratories, with load-frame calibration logs and specimen geometry measurements reviewed post hoc to characterise variability — a workflow consistent with an observational characterisation of the test population rather than a prospectively controlled experiment. The narrative throughout this package treats this activity as satisfying the controlled-experiment requirement because the physical testing itself was conducted on a standardised fixture; however, the structured activityType field reflects the actual conduct of the evidence-gathering activity.",
      "quantitativeOutcome": "Max QoI deviation 7.3%; max E/uval 1.61; all acceptance criteria satisfied.",
      "wasGeneratedBy": {
