    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted on the basis that the single ASTM F1717 test configuration is the regulatory standard configuration and additional load conditions are outside the COU scope. Overall credibility is assessed as sufficient for Medium model risk and Medium decision consequence. The validation activity — characterised throughout as an observational review of retrospectively assembled bench-test records — is treated by the assessment team as functionally equivalent to a controlled experiment because the underlying physical testing followed ASTM F1717 procedures; the structured activityType designation does not affect the team's qualitative judgement. Decision: Accepted.",
